cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.DL, cs.SD, cs.CY 

The paper explores the structural properties of the network generated by the editorial activities of the members of “Information Science & Library Science” journals, which involves the use of network analysis techniques. This suggests that the paper could belong to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: 

- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - as the paper focuses on analyzing the network of editorial boards in the field of Information Science and Library Science. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) - as the paper discusses the editorial policies of journals in the field of Information Science and Library Science, which involves the retrieval of relevant information. 
- cs.DL (Digital Libraries) - as the paper deals with the editorial activities of journals in the field of Library Science, which is closely related to digital libraries. 
- cs.SD (Software Development) - as the paper may involve the use of software tools for network analysis techniques. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) - as the paper may discuss the impact of the network of editorial boards on the field of Information Science and Library Science, which has implications for society.
